				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Alright, I'll admit that this is incredibly tangential to &quot;Dark and Stormy&quot; as a theme, but I'll be damned if making &quot;The World War I Flying Ace&quot; into an SCP article, one with a fair amount of heart and emotional impact, doesn't bring a smile to my face.</p> <p>+1 MMG.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5305481#post-3719880</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5305481/scp-3952#post-3719880</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 23 Feb 2018 13:22:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I don't think a cubic measurement makes sense. A measurement of area tells the in-universe reader roughly where this operates and by extension how many people might see this and how much trouble it would take to hide. Adding height into the mix removes this information (if the flight altitude wasn't specified, which adds additional fluff).</p> <p>For example, if you were asked where a particular type of bird lives, your answer would be in square km.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
